Childrenâ€™s Linguistic Feedback

Masoud Jasbi

4/12/2017

## for bootstrapping 95% confidence intervals
theta <- function(x,xdata) {mean(xdata[x])}
ci.low <- function(x) {
  quantile(bootstrap(1:length(x),1000,theta,x)$thetastar,.025)}
ci.high <- function(x) {
  quantile(bootstrap(1:length(x),1000,theta,x)$thetastar,.975)}

Method

The study uses the same paradigm as Jasbi & Frank (2017). The only difference is the dependent variable. Jasbi & Frank use a three-dlevel reward variable: A big star, a small star and a circle. The big star means the puppet was right, the small star means the puppet was a little bit right, and the circle means the puppet was not right.

Procedure

In this study we only ask children to verbally correct the puppet.

Annotation

Childrenâ€™s responses are coded as â€œ0â€ if the child resonded with â€œYes! Thatâ€™s rightâ€ and 1 if the child said â€œNo!â€ and provided the right guess.

Results

Linguistic Feedback

Non-Critical Trials

x2_data <- read.csv("../2_processed_data/feedback_children_data")

feedback_noncritical <- 
  x2_data %>%
  select(-TVJT) %>%
  filter(critical==0) %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  group_by(id, Animal, Guess, feedback) %>%
  summarise(counts= n()) %>%
  spread(feedback, counts) %>%
  replace(is.na(.), 0) %>%
  mutate(total = J + D + C) %>%
  gather(feedback, counts, J:C) %>%
  mutate(prop = counts / total) %>%
  group_by(Animal, Guess, feedback) %>%
  summarize(cih = ci.high(prop),
            cil = ci.low(prop),
            prop = mean(prop)) 

judgement_noncritical <- 
  x2_data %>%
  select(-TVJT) %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  filter(critical==0) %>%
  group_by(id, Animal, Guess, judgement) %>%
  summarise(counts= n()) %>%
  spread(judgement, counts) %>%
  replace(is.na(.), 0) %>%
  mutate(total = `0` + N + Y) %>%
  gather(judgement, counts, `0`:Y) %>%
  mutate(prop = counts / total) %>%
  group_by(Animal, Guess, judgement) %>%
  summarize(cih = ci.high(prop),
            cil = ci.low(prop),
            prop = mean(prop)) 

correction_noncritical <- 
  x2_data %>%
  select(-TVJT) %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  filter(critical==0) %>%
  group_by(id, Animal, Guess, correction) %>%
  summarise(counts= n()) %>%
  spread(correction, counts) %>%
  replace(is.na(.), 0) %>%
  mutate(total = `0` + E + I) %>%
  gather(correction, counts, `0`:I) %>%
  mutate(prop = counts / total) %>%
  group_by(Animal, Guess, correction) %>%
  summarize(cih = ci.high(prop),
            cil = ci.low(prop),
            prop = mean(prop)) 
ggplot(feedback_noncritical, 
       aes(x=feedback, y=prop)) + 
  geom_bar(stat="identity", width = 0.6, position="dodge") + 
  geom_linerange(aes(ymax = cih, ymin = cil)) + 
  facet_grid(Guess~Animal) + 
  guides(fill=FALSE) + 
  labs(title = "", x = "", y = "") + 
  theme_few() + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90, hjust = 1, vjust = .5)) +
  scale_fill_solarized()

ggplot(judgement_noncritical, 
       aes(x=judgement, y=prop)) +

Truth Value Judgements

tvjt_noncritical <-
  x2_data %>%
  filter(critical==0) %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  group_by(id, Animal, Guess, TVJT) %>%
  summarise(counts= n()) %>%
  spread(TVJT, counts) %>%
  replace(is.na(.), 0) %>%
  mutate(total = `1` + `0`) %>%
  gather(TVJT, counts, `0`:`1`) %>%
  mutate(prop = counts / total) %>%
  group_by(Animal, Guess, TVJT) %>%
  summarize(cih = ci.high(prop),
            cil = ci.low(prop),
            prop = mean(prop)) 
ggplot(tvjt_noncritical, 
       aes(x=TVJT, y=prop)) + 
  geom_bar(stat="identity", width = 0.6, position="dodge") + 
  geom_linerange(aes(ymax = cih, ymin = cil)) + 
  facet_grid(Guess~Animal) + 
  guides(fill=FALSE) + 
  labs(title = "", x = "", y = "") + 
  theme_few() + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90, hjust = 1, vjust = .5)) +
  scale_fill_solarized()
